Program: Outlook
Title: 15/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00pfhqw
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 19 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Palestinians Rita Ishaq in Gaza and Taher Musilmani in Northern Israel tell us how they fell in love despite not being able to meet. Also, French windsurfing champion Sarah Hebert on why she had to abandon her attempt to cross the Atlantic from Senegal to Guadeloupe. And a Somali community worker in London describes how khat has devastated her family. Show less